TEE YIH JIA FOOD HUB (MAIN CONTRACT)
PROPOSED ERECTION OF 9-STOREY INDUSTRIAL FACTORY (TEE YIH JIA FOOD HUB) WITH SINGLE STOREY COLDROOM AND DRY STORE ON LOTS (01555WPT, 01555KPT, 01663LPT, 03911V, 01634CPT, 01631NPT) MK 13 AT SENOKO DRIVE / SENOKO ROAD 

RE:	LETTER OF ACCEPTANCE: SUB-CONTRACT FOR SUPPLY OF LABOUR, SMALL TOOLS AND EQUIPMENT FOR RC STRUCTURAL WORKS TO BUILDING BLOCK AND EXTERNAL WORKS 

1.0	AWARD
We refer to the above captioned and are pleased to confirm that you have been awarded this Sub-Contract subject to the approval of the Architect.

2.0	SUB-CONTRACT SUM
The Sub-Contract Sum shall be at Singapore Dollars: Three Million Six Hundred Forty Five Thousand Four Hundred Twenty Seven and Cents Fifty Only (S$3,645,427.50) which shall be subject to re-measurement in accordance with the attached Sub-Contract Schedule of Rates, which shall remain firm and fixed throughout the Main Contract Period including any extension of time thereafter.
All variation works shall be based on a “back-to-back” condition and the prices shall be mutually agreed and confirmed by us in writing prior to the commencement of the variation works. However, in the event that the variation works are required to proceed first due to its urgency, you shall proceed immediately upon the Main Contractor’s written request pending the valuation of your variation works.
The Sub-Contract Sum shall be deemed to include for all costs and expenses relating to Goods and Services Tax (GST) payable by you on the purchase of the goods and services necessary for execution, completion and maintenance of the works.  Such costs and expenses shall extend to, but not limited to administrative costs, financial charges and any loss of input tax and the like relating to GST payable by you.
GST payable by the Main Contractor is excluded. The Main Contractor shall bear any GST payable under Goods and Services Tax Act (Chapter 117A) in respect of the Contract Sum only.
No adjustment to the Sub-Contract Schedule of Rates shall be allowed for any fluctuations in the cost of labour, materials, equipment and / or services, taxes (except GST), interest, levies, etc. that may be incurred during the original or extended Contract Period.
In the event that there is an extension of time granted to the Main Contractor, you shall not be entitled to claim for your own extra preliminaries due to the prolonged construction period.

3.0	SCOPE OF WORKS
The scope of the Sub-Contract Works shall include the provision of all labour, small construction tools and everything necessary, whether of a temporary or permanent nature, to carry out and complete the RC structural works to factory building block and external works including any other works deemed necessary for the proper execution of this Sub-Contract in accordance with the Conditions of Contract, Specifications and Contract Drawings of the Main Contract and the Main Contractor’s Programme including any revision thereof to the satisfaction and approval of the Architect.
The scope of works / Sub-Contract Sum shall also include but not limited to the followings:-
General for Formwork, Rebars, Concreting and Precast Works
a.	Provision of all the preliminaries, overheads, overtime pay, CPF contribution, Foreign Worker’s Levy, Skill Development Fund, BCA coretrade trainings and etc under the Sub-Contract Works except items otherwise noted to be provided by the Main Contractor as per attached “Appendix 1”.
b.	You shall participate in a handing-over inspection of the completed structure works together with the Main Contractor. All defects and discrepancies shall be highlighted at the inspection. You shall fully responsible to remedy, rectify or making good any of such defects.
c.	You shall check all construction drawings and shop drawings including architectural, structural and M&E drawings and highlight the discrepancy if any, before execution of the works. Failure, you shall bear any cost for abortive works involved.
d.	You shall respond to our Project Director / Project Manager’s instructions to commence work on site or attend to any related matter within 24 hours from the instruction, verbal or written.
e.	You shall apply same unit rate for formwork, rebar and concreting to RC beams and pourstrips, if precast plank is used. Toppings and installation of precast plank shall be price separately.
f.	You shall appoint a competent full time Site Representative who shall act on behalf of your organisation and appoint a permanent member to the EHS (Environment, Health & Safety) Committee. Such representative shall attend the scheduled site meetings, the monthly Safety Committee Meeting, the safety inspection as and when required, failing which a penalty of S$300.00 will be imposed for every absence from the scheduled meetings and the Main Contractor shall reserve the right to deduct such amount from your interim payments.
g.	You shall provide full time rigger and signal man, lifting supervisor for your Sub-Contract Works.
h.	You shall provide a safety supervisor, formwork safety supervisor first aider during the whole period of your Sub-Contract Works in accordance to Ministry of Manpower’s (MOM) safety requirements. 
i.	The Main Contractor will provide Surveyor for setting out of the grid line and elevation level, upon which, you are to have your own competent surveyor for setting out of your Sub-Contract works and ensure the accuracy of the works.
j.	You shall be responsible to check and submit the following quality check record to Main Contractor:-
i)	Before casting
1)	Internal verticality of column and wall
2)	Soffit level of plank / beam and slab
3)	External verticality using laser plumb and any other checks required by Consultant.
ii)	After casting
1)	Slab casting level (one day after slab casting)
2)	Soffit level of plank / beam and slab (within 5 days after dismantling of formwork)
3)	Internal verticality of column and wall (within 5 days after dismantling of formwork) and any other checks required by Consultant.
k.	The Sub-Contractor shall at his own cost, comply with the Main Contractor’s instructions to carry out any overtime or night work whenever necessary, without further claim against the Main Contractor. Work activities that are likely to generate noise that exceed the permissible noise level are not allowed after 10.00pm or at any time imposed by the Authorities on any day. Any penalty from Authorities due to noise generated by your work will be back-charged to you.
l.	You shall co-ordinate with other Sub-Contractors in the interfacing works especially I-beam installer / M&E Sub-Contractor during M&E provision installation and the waterproofing Sub-Contractor. If necessary, including more than one operation of your works in the same locations.
m.	Provision of adequate and approved protection (materials shall be provided by Main Contractor) to your installed works during construction and after installation until handing over to the Main Contractor. E.g. laying of protection to staircase riser with plywood.
n.	Provision of adequate care and precaution to existing works for other trades especially M&E installation, with suitable materials. Any claim by the relevant parties made to the Main Contractor, will be back-charged to you.
o.	The Sub-Contract Works shall include all labour and equipment to transport all materials from storage / ground level to the respective work areas unless otherwise noted in the “Appendix 1”.
p.	You shall submit your material request form 10 days in advance prior to take delivery of materials for your works. The original delivery order with your site representative’s signature shall be returned to our store keeper the next day for recording purposes.
q.	You shall bear the cost of touching up, making good all defects including final finishing works and any other related abortive work caused by your failure to comply fully with construction drawings and specifications. You shall not hack any structure without prior approval and not rectify any honeycombs concrete without prior inspection. You shall provide all materials for repair works and polymer mortar for external wall defect rectification work at no cost to us. You shall conduct structural water-ponding test for all wet areas after concreting and rectify the leakage as per the method statement which was approved by the Consultant.
r.	The Main Contractor shall provide disposal bins at designated area. You shall clear all your materials and debris of each storey and bring down to the disposal bins at ground floor when instructed by the Main-Contractor and thoroughly clean up your work areas upon completion.
s.	You shall assign sufficient supervisors / workers to attend handing over inspection as required by the Main Contractor to the satisfaction of the Architect.
t.	You shall assign at least 3 certified coretrade foremen and 2 certified coretrade supervisor, and to sign the attendance daily.



Concreting
a.	Concreting of all cast in-situ reinforced concrete work.
b.	Concreting of lintels, lintel beams, stiffeners, kerbs, plinths, machine base, concrete blocks, doghouse, nibs, projections, features, ledges, downhang walls, drop panels, gutters, humps, stanchions, pre-formed columns, 100mm high concrete heel stone and works of the similar nature, which may be required to be carried out outside the sequence of the Main Contract work and/or different operations / stages shall be included and priced in accordance with the Schedule of Rate.
c.	Casting of kickers to wall, columns and other vertical structural members.
d.	Taking delivery, hoisting and compacting concrete in positions including preparing surfaces of concrete to receive fresh concrete.
e.	Tamping and/or vibration of concrete to give adequate compaction according to the specifications.
f.	Preparing and providing construction joints including roughening of edges, the Sub-Contractor shall be responsible for the maintenance of the construction joints to the satisfaction of the Architect and/or the Main Contractor. The Sub-Contractor shall bear all costs for any repair works required.
g.	Pour joints, forming and cutting rebates, grooves, chases, mortices, holes, openings not exceeding 0.10m2 and any other sundry items of the like nature.
h.	Provide labour to apply curing compound on casted concrete.
i.	Working in between and around reinforcement bars.
j.	Trimming, levelling and compacting excavated surfaces to the required level to receive lean concrete/concrete.
k.	Laying on any types of sub-base, cleaning and preparing surfaces to receive screed, paving rendering, etc.
l.	Preparing of surfaces including levelling to receive floor hardener, whether sprinkled or brushed on, and other finishes. Power floating shall be carried out by others.
m.	Trowel top of concrete surface to requires levels/slopes/falls.
n.	Laying in bays including all labour associated with projecting rebars and placing of materials for construction joint.
o.	Installation, dismantling and cleaning of concrete buckets and pump pipes (vertical and horizontal) after each operation.
p.	Covering of trench of lift pit / consumer switch room with plywood and concrete.
q.	Provide all necessary equipment and tools including vibrators, wheel barrows and concrete pails for the Sub-Contractor’s operation. Fuel shall be supplied by Main Contractor.
r.	Provide labour and materials to remove and touch up all blisters, honeycombs, cracks, etc, with approved construction grout (material by Main-Contractor).
s.	Removal of remaining concrete by washing with water to a designated location after each operation.
t.	Undertake that the wastage of concrete would not exceed 5% and lean concrete would not exceed 15% of the measured quantities, the Sub-Contractor shall bear the cost for any wastage in excess of the agreed percentage.
u.	Submit a breakdown of your concrete work done with sufficient drawings together with your progress claim to the Main Contractor for the assessment of your claim.
v.	Full attendance of competent foreman and workmen during inspection of formwork and/or concreting as instructed by the Main Contractor.
w.	Provide a competent supervisor on standby for night casting.
x.	All other items not specifically mentioned herein but necessary for the due and proper execution and completion of the work.
y.	Upon completion of Sub-Contract works, Sub-Contractor is to clean up the concrete surface free from debris, nails, formworks and hand over to Main Contractor.

Rebars / Steel Welded Mesh
a.	All cleaning, placing and tying of rebars and welded mesh including the provision of all necessary tying wire, concrete cover support, bar chair, temporary fixing and/or supports for the Sub-Contract Works. Bent bar chair for basement slab using rebar shall be provided by Main Contractor.
b.	Fixing, straightening and adjustment of starter bars at any location especially for construction joint areas for rebars and welded mesh including removal of box-up materials, especially at lift shaft area by using jump form method.
c.	Fixing of reinforcement bar and welded mesh, fixing for temporary openings/enclosures and its subsequent casting back.
d.	Fixing of starter bars, pull-out starter bars, and/or other starter bar system for slabs & beams are not considered as measurable items. They shall not be treated as construction wastage also.
e.	Fixing of rebars to stiffeners, kerbs, plinths, machine base, concrete blocks, doghouse, nibs, projections, features, ledges, downhang walls, drop panels, gutters, humps, stanchions and works of the similar nature shall be included.
f.	Fixing of trimmer bars or cutting of rebars, if so required, around all openings, M&E services/ducts, pipe sleeves, cast-in plates and other works of the similar nature.
g.	Cleaning starter bars, lapping and other associated works at construction joint; lapping of rebar shall not be included in the measurement of rebar for slabs & beams. They shall not be treated as construction wastage also.
h.	Taking delivery, unloading and storing of straight and/or fabricated materials.
i.	Erection of scaffolding for assembling of reinforcement bars and welded mesh.
j.	Labour for transportation and shifting of all straight and/or fabricated materials, equipment, tools, etc both horizontally and vertically.
k.	Erection, relocation and maintenance of fabrication yards and working tables. The Main Contractor shall provide the Sub-Contractor with one set of bar cutting machine, one set of bending machine and fuel for the machines.
l.	Prepare bar bending schedule (BBS) to show the work that have been completed and attach these with your progress claim to submit to the Main Contractor for assessment of your claim.
m.	The Sub-Contractor undertakes that the wastage for rebar would not exceed 3% for cut & bend and 5% for straight bar. Any wastage in excess shall be borne by the Sub-Contractor.
n.	You shall record down any additional rebar / wire mesh required by Consultant with their endorsement.
o.	Steel welded mesh to be measured net, no allowance for lap.
p.	Full attendance of competent workmen during concreting to take instructions from the Main Contractor.
q.	Provide all necessary tools and power tools including fixing pins.
r.	Erection of scaffolding for assembling of reinforcement bars and welded mesh and erection of accessway for Resident Engineer/RTO inspection.
s.	All other items not specifically mentioned herein but necessary for the due and proper execution and completion of the work.

Formwork
a.	The Sub-Contract works shall include the provision of labour, small construction tools, and equipments to carry out and complete all the formwork for RC structural works including any other works deemed necessary for the proper execution of this Sub-Contract in accordance with the Conditions of Contract and Specifications of the Main Contract.
b.	Form door openings, lift openings, boxing-up for M&E services, pouring strips and the like nature in walls, core walls and slabs.
c.	Kickers to walls, columns and other vertical structural members.
d.	Expanded metal in pour strip, stop end and construction joints shall be provided by Main Contractor and installed by the Sub-Contractor.
e.	Form construction joints including related work to receive starter bars and/or waterstops and/or hyribs (materials provided by Main Contractor).
f.	All notching, allowance for overlaps and passing at angles, battens, strutting, bolting, wedging, easing, forming splay edges, fillers, narrow edges and arises including drilling holes for starter bars, striking and removal.
g.	All construction joints, rebates, corner angle guards, holes for starter bars and all incidental works for the casting of concrete. Hack and roughen the construction joints after casting of concrete.
h.	Filling of gaps to prevent concrete leakage. The Sub-Contractor shall be responsible for all cleaning in the event of any leakage and rectification of formwork.
i.	Patching up of indentations after the removal of form ties. Patching up material to be supplied by the Main Contractor. 
j.	Polyfoam or other materials for forming of openings, if required, shall be supplied by the Main Contractor and installed by Sub-Contractor without charges.
k.	Erect working platforms, railings, toe-boards, temporary stairs, safety device etc. (materials supplied by the Main Contractor) for inspection and usage of the same by other sub-contractors for reinforcement bars, concreting, etc.
l.	All machineries, equipment and special tool for fixing and dismantling of formwork.
m.	Hoisting and shifting both horizontally and vertically of the materials, associated equipment and accessories and stack the same in a proper manner at locations designated by the Main Contractor upon completion of the work.
n.	Full attendance of competent supervisor(s) and standby adequate carpenters during inspection of formwork and concreting as instructed by the Main Contractor.
o.	Cleaning of all formworks, application of mould oil and other preparatory works to be ready for concreting.
p.	The marking of the base grid lines and base level shall be given by the Main Contractor. Detail setting out shall be done by the Sub-Contractor.
q.	Formwork to construction joints (non-measurable) including preparation works for fixing starter bars such as construction joints and its subsequent removal.
r.	Re-propping of casted areas after dismantling of formwork, as and when directed by the Main Contractor.
s.	Fixing and removal of formwork for kickers to columns, walls and other vertical structural members.
t.	You shall observe strictly the schedules for striking formworks in the specification or safe work procedure, failing which a penalty of S$1,000.00 will be imposed to you.
u.	All other items not specifically mentioned herein but necessary for the due and proper execution and completion of the work.
v.	Upon completion of Sub-Contract works, the Sub-Contractor is to clean and tidy up the materials such as metalform, u-clips, plywood, scaffold frames and hand over to the Main Contractor.
w.	Undertake that the wastage of metalform and U-clip would not exceed 5% and 10% respectively of the measured quantities, the Sub-Contractor shall bear the cost for any wastage in excess of the agreed percentage.
x.	Submit a breakdown of your formwork work done together with your progress claim to the Main Contractor for the assessment of your claim.
y.	Erect temporary working platform and barricade over construction joint due to the sequence of construction.
z.	Plywood and timber materials shall be recycled for at least five (5) times.
aa.	Formwork for stiffeners, kerbs plinths, machine base, doghouse, nibs, projections, features, ledge, downhung, walls, drops, gutters, humps and the works of similar nature shall be included and to be measured in accordance with the Schedule of Rate.

Installation of Precast Components
a.	The Sub-Contract Works for precast components shall include labour for the checking of precast quality, verticality, installation and grouting of precast components. Grouting material shall be provided by Main Contractor.
b.	Unloading of precast component to the stock stand provided on site.

SUBMISSIONS
