c.	You shall submit work statements for Work Safety Procedure, Risks Management and WSHA including any other documents for our review before commencement of site works. You shall ensure all your site personnel and site works comply fully with our in house EHSS Rules and Regulations including Authorities / Statutory legislation of MOM, MOH, EMA, SCDF, NEA, etc. Failing which, Main Contractor reserves the right to impose penalties for non-compliances and deduct the same from your interim payment.

QUALITY CONTROL
a.	You shall comply within your scope of works at no cost to the proposed method of construction to meet the CONQUAS target as required in the Main Contract and when instructed by the Main Contractor.
b.	You shall be responsible for all inspections, quality control as per Main Contract requirements in respect to your works.
c.	You shall attend fully to CONQUAS Assessment and comply fully with the Main Contractor’s directions on QAQC matters.
d.	The Structural Quality Standard and Workmanship under your Sub-Contract Works shall be as follows:-
i)	Ceiling soffit slant ≤ 3mm within the room
ii)	Beam soffit slant ≤ 3mm/1.2m or 10mm
iii)	Verticality plumb tolerance ≤ 3mm /1.0 or 10mm
iv)	Wall or Beam corners ≤ 4mm per 300mm
v)	Deviation from intended slab top level (Slab casted surface):10mm
You shall comply strictly to above Structural Quality Standard. Failing to do so, you shall bear the cost of labour and materials (e.g. prepacked materials) for touching up, making good all defects including final finishing works. A sum of money shall be retained and released to you upon your completion of rectification works to the satisfaction of Architect.


PROVISION BY MAIN CONTRACTOR
a.	Passenger cum material hoist for your Sub-Contract Works will be provided by the Main Contractor. You shall provide workers to transport all materials and tools to the execution of the works to the working areas. You shall assign your workers to attend the lesson on the operation of passenger hoist conducted by our supplier and your responsibility to assign your own worker to operate the hoist after 7.00pm.
b.	The Main Contractor will only provide climbing access platform with netting and toe board for external building perimeter, supply of angle brackets and timber plank inside lift shafts for the purpose of safety access in accordance with MOM requirement. You shall deploy your workers to lift the climbing access platform with the assistance of tower crane, install and dismantle of brackets and timber plank for lift shaft opening including patching up holes after dismantling. You shall also be responsible for installation of barricade to all open sides of the building at construction level until handed over to Main Contractor including cover up all floor opening and cleaning of peripheral shelter.
c.	Provision and erection of scaffolding, access, props, supports, working platform complete with barricade or any temporary works below 4.0m high required by your Sub-Contract Works shall be at your own cost. The Main contractor shall provide the scaffold material. You shall return all the scaffold material to us upon completion of your Sub-contract works.
d.	The Main Contractor will provide only temporary power and utility points and lighting to access ways. You shall tapped off from such points and provide all necessary power points, spotlights and localized lighting for your Sub-Contract Works including extension for water hose and cable.
e.	The Main Contractor will provide temporary DB at alternate floors.
f.	Adequate storage space / store will be provided to you on site. However, Main Contractor is not responsible for the loss or damage of the material or equipment kept in the storage space / store.

